description: I remember the first time I saw one. It must have been a few of days after the Peliad meteor shower. He didn't have a costume. He didn't have a cape-he just appeared in the sky as a commercial airliner was going down. The woman next to me yelled, "Look! Up in the sky!" And that's when he crushed the plane like a beer can. We had no idea how bad things were going to get. These days, I just pray for mercy.

I had no idea that she was one of them. She was hot ? she had a killer body, stacked and ripped. A gym girl. I was thinking "Okay" until I saw her face pierced. She's just sitting there, minding her own business, eating a plate of eggs. When that guy whistled at her, she turned into an animal. Leapt out of her seat and punched him - clean through the wall. Killed him with a slap. That was when I knew everything had changed
1-Shot release by Fun Publications as a continuation of the Shattered Glass Universe.

description: The epic storyline from fan-favorites Kurt Busiek, Carlos Pacheco and Jesus Merino concludes in this volume collecting SUPERMAN #662-664, 667 and SUPERMAN ANNUAL #13! The Man of Steel defends Metropolis from harm, but now he faces a dilemma: Are his heroics only making things worse? It all leads to a brawl between Superman and Arion of Atlantis miles beneath the Atlantic! But can Superman's Kryptonian might stand up to the magic of a sorcerer? And what will the outcome of the battle mean for the fate of the world?
name: Vol. 2
